 suggestion would be something more along the lines of 'du -h', but it's just my opinion.\r\n\r\nhttp://alvinalexander.com/unix/edu/examples/du.shtml"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/10851224","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/633#issuecomment-10851224","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/633","id":10851224,"user":{"login":"dehoeninger","id":2651984,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/bea86ce4b0a1e2137554d422b7d29d6b?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f7da0ecf309eb016736690919be53278b.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"bea86ce4b0a1e2137554d422b7d29d6b","url":"https://api.github.com/users/dehoeninger","html_url":"https://github.com/dehoeninger","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dehoeninger/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dehoeninger/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dehoeninger/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dehoeninger/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dehoeninger/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dehoeninger/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dehoeninger/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dehoeninger/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dehoeninger/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2012-11-29t15:27:35z","updated_at":"2012-11-29t15:27:35z","body":"i've to agree with @andredasilvapinto\r\n\r\nthe \">1000\" isn't very usefull. and due to the fact, that a more accurate rounded value doesn't confusing a user at all, there should be no reason for those agressive information hiding."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/10869670","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/633#issuecomment-10869670","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/633","id":10869670,"user":{"login":"jancborchardt","id":925062,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/2fd3f4d5d762955e5b603794a888fa97?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f84ec51f9ceed468217d4e13abf78da9c.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"2fd3f4d5d762955e5b603794a888fa97","url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt","html_url":"https://github.com/jancborchardt","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2012-11-29t22:34:26z","updated_at":"2012-11-29t22:34:26z","body":"hey folks! regarding directories, this seems like a good point actually, good catch.\r\n\r\n* one thing weâ€™re _not_ going to do is mix cardinalities, say put â»8.8 gbâ« there. â»du -hâ« and actually most other file managers make it hard to work with filesize because everything is mixed: k, b, mb, gb etc.\r\n* we could say for folders it should always show the exact mb value â»8796â« but that looks messy, and itâ€™s not the point to show the _exact_ value. that is provided on hover.\r\n* we could round to 100s, and show â»~8800â« in that case. it would provide enough clue to know if the folder was uploaded entirely (also because you have to hover for the last details anyway, and desktop file managers only show folder sizes in properties).\r\n\r\nlast one seems best. thoughts? also @raydiation "},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/10870650","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/633#issuecomment-10870650","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/633","id":10870650,"user":{"login":"raydiation","id":195053,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/aa0d7b7302e0d7f4f9513c23b571383a?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2faf0a25e27510f77d97634a6bbe653b13.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"aa0d7b7302e0d7f4f9513c23b571383a","url":"https://api.github.com/users/raydiation","html_url":"https://github.com/raydiation","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/raydiation/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/raydiation/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/raydiation/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/raydiation/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/raydiation/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/raydiation/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/raydiation/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/raydiation/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/raydiation/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2012-11-29t23:01:29z","updated_at":"2012-11-29t23:01:29z","body":"i looked at reference art like google drive and dropbox. they dont show filesize at all (maybe because they depend on you paying them for space :d?)\r\n\r\ni was thinking about stuff like game isos or bigger files like hd movies with 30 gb. do we really want to display ~30000mb? that seems to be hard to read. i'd actually vote in favor of mixed cardinalities and only use one comma digit for precision like 15.6 gb. \r\n\r\npeople are used to see this from ads (smartphone 8gb space) and i think expect it from a filebrowser. also to make something useful out of that information i think its important to give the user a feedback on how full the harddisk (or quota) is currently like displaying a progressbar at the bottom.\r\n\r\ni think the question is: does the user want/need direct information on how big his files are. open for discussion.\r\n\r\njust my 2â¢\r\n"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/10872030","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/633#issuecomment-10872030","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/633","id":10872030,"user":{"login":"andredasilvapinto","id":2671593,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/49696504a1bf5d049faf2cf2da32e57b?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2ffeedc303bc35c3174f6fb66d896da2d0.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"49696504a1bf5d049faf2cf2da32e57b","url":"https://api.github.com/users/andredasilvapinto","html_url":"https://github.com/andredasilvapinto","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/andredasilvapinto/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/andredasilvapinto/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/andredasilvapinto/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/andredasilvapinto/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/andredasilvapinto/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/andredasilvapinto/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/andredasilvapinto/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/andredasilvapinto/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/andredasilvapinto/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2012-11-29t23:43:16z","updated_at":"2012-11-29t23:43:16z","body":"i subscribe what raydiation said. one of the things i immediately did was to check dropbox's approach too.\r\n\r\nregarding the want/need for that information, i can only talk for myself and my opinion is already on this thread, let's see what others think."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/10872315","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/633#issuecomment-10872315","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/633","id":10872315,"user":{"login":"jancborchardt","id":925062,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/2fd3f4d5d762955e5b603794a888fa97?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f84ec51f9ceed468217d4e13abf78da9c.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"2fd3f4d5d762955e5b603794a888fa97","url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt","html_url":"https://github.com/jancborchardt","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2012-11-29t23:53:30z","updated_at":"2012-11-29t23:55:15z","body":"on fri, nov 30, 2012 at 12:01 am, bernhard posselt <notifications@github.com\r\n> wrote:\r\n\r\n> i looked at reference art like google drive and dropbox. they dont show\r\n> filesize at all (maybe because they depend on you paying them for space\r\n> :d?)\r\n>\r\nthey donâ€™t show it because they want to make file size not matter. just\r\nupload anything, itâ€™ll be alright. file size introduces the constant\r\nawareness that something is big and takes up space and you might want to\r\ndelete it to free up space (= also save less on dropbox/gdrive).\r\n\r\n\r\n>\r\n> i was thinking about stuff like game isos or bigger files like hd movies\r\n> with 30 gb. do we really want to display ~30000mb? that seems to be hard to\r\n> read. i'd actually vote in favor of mixed cardinalities and only use one\r\n> comma digit for precision like 15.6 gb.\r\n>\r\nweâ€™d display ~30.000 then. except we wouldnâ€™t, because itâ€™s a file and then\r\nit would be >1000.\r\n\r\n\r\n>\r\n>  people are used to see this from ads (smartphone 8gb space) and i think\r\n> expect it from a filebrowser. also to make something useful out of that\r\n> information i think its important to give the user a feedback on how full\r\n> the harddisk (or quota) is currently like displaying a progressbar at the\r\n> bottom.\r\n>\r\nthe gb from ads seems like a good point.\r\n\r\nregarding quota bar: referencing what i said above about dropbox and google\r\ndrive â€“ we donâ€™t want to hide file size completely, but we also donâ€™t want\r\nto push quota in peopleâ€™s faces. quota is only important if itâ€™s close to\r\nrunning out, and then we can still display a notification. but it shouldnâ€™t\r\nbe a constant â»hey buddy you use 2gb of your available 20gb, just so you\r\nknowâ« (hyperbole).\r\n\r\n\r\n>\r\n> i think the question is: does the user want/need direct information on how\r\n> big his files are. open for discussion.\r\n>\r\nwhat i found out in initial research was that this was mainly important for\r\nknowing if itâ€™s fast to download/upload and if it can be sent via email. so\r\ni think this is valuable enough. of course i know what dropbox and google drive do,\r\nbut as mentioned above they have different motivations.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nactually now iâ€™m leaning more again to just keeping it at >1000. if you\r\nreally want to know more, just hover it. itâ€™s not that important â€“\r\nespecially if you just need to do it once to check if the whole folder\r\nuploaded."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/10886535","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/633#issuecomment-10886535","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/633","id":10886535,"user":{"login":"raydiation","id":195053,"avatar_url":"https:/